        <p><center><h1>Our Method</h1>For many, the process of quitting smoking is a long one. We believe in full customization of specific steps to reach that 
        goal. We propose a plan called the 30 day challenge that focuses on key points to get you on the road of recovery.</center></p>
        <dl>
            <center><dt><h3>Week 1</h3></dt></center>
                <center><dd>Try to delay the first cigarette of the day for as long as possible</dd></center>
                <center><dd>Try to limit to one cigarette per hour</dd></center>
                <center><dd>Make a conscious effort to stay away from cigarettes</dd></center>
            <center><dt><h3>Week 2</h3></dt></center>
                <center><dd>Try to delay the first cigarette of the day for as long as possible</dd></center>
                <center><dd>Try to limit to one cigarette every two hours</dd></center>
                <center><dd>Make a conscious effort to stay away from cigarettes</dd></center>
            <center><dt><h3>Week </h3></dt></center>
                <center><dd>Switch to light cigarettes and if you have already, switch to ultra light</dd></center>
                <center><dd>Try to delay the first cigarette of the day for as long as possible</dd></center>
                <center><dd>Try to limit to one cigarette every three hours</dd></center>
                <center><dd>Make a conscious effort to stay away from cigarettes</dd></center>
            <center><dt><h3>Week 4</h3></dt></center>
                <center><dd>Switch or continue with ultra light</dd></center>
                <center><d>Try to delay the first cigarette of the day as long as possible</dd></center>
                <center><dd>Try to limit to one cigarette every four hours</dd></center>
            </dt>
        </dl>
